Package: RidgeRegCuda
Type: Package
Title: CUDA-Accelerated Ridge Regression with Scaling and Permutation Testing
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-04-18
Authors@R: c(
    person("Seongyong Park", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "seongyong.park@nih.gov",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4533-3071"))
  )
Maintainer: Seongyong Park <seongyong.park@nih.gov> 
Description: Provides high-performance ridge regression computations using
    NVIDIA CUDA for GPU acceleration. Supports dense input matrices (X) and
    either dense or sparse matrices (dgCMatrix format via the 'Matrix'
    package) for the response variable (Y). Includes GPU-accelerated
    functions for standard (dense) and sparse-aware column scaling. Offers
    permutation testing for assessing coefficient significance (t-test
    functionality has been removed). Leverages NVIDIA libraries (cuBLAS,
    cuSOLVER, cuSPARSE, cuRAND) for optimal performance on compatible GPUs.
    Includes utility functions for CUDA device management and GPU memory
    estimation.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Imports:
    methods,
    Matrix
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    reticulate,
    ggplot2,
    microbenchmark
URL: https://github.com/psychemistz/RidgeRegCuda
BugReports: https://github.com/psychemistz/RidgeRegCuda/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
SystemRequirements: NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit (>= 11.0 recommended, check library compatibility),
    NVIDIA GPU Driver,
    Supported NVIDIA GPU (Compute Capability >= 6.0 recommended for double precision)
NeedsCompilation: yes
